# Estándares de Código PHP 8.2

## PHP General

- **Versión**: PHP 8.2+ recomendado
- **Estándar**: Seguir **PSR-12** (evolución de PSR-2)
- **Nombres de clases**: PascalCase (ej: `CommonHelper`, `WoocommerceAdmin`)
- **Nombres de funciones**: snake_case (ej: `get_user_friendly_schedule_info()`)
- **Nombres de variables**: snake_case o camelCase (consistente en el proyecto)
- **Constantes**: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- **Espaciado**: 4 espacios (no tabs)
- **Líneas máximas**: 120 caracteres recomendado

## Características PHP 8.2

### Readonly Classes

```php
// ✅ Clases readonly - todas las propiedades son readonly
readonly class User {
    public function __construct(
        public string $id,
        public string $name,
        public string $email,
        public DateTime $createdAt
    ) {}
}

// Uso
$user = new User('123', 'John', 'john@example.com', new DateTime());
// $user->name = 'Jane'; // Error: no se puede modificar
```

### Disjunctive Normal Form (DNF) Types

```php
// ✅ Tipos complejos con DNF
function process((A&B)|null $value): (X&Y)|null {
    // ...
}

// Ejemplo práctico
function save((\PDO&\LoggerInterface)|null $connection): void {
    if ($connection instanceof \PDO) {
        // Guardar en base de datos
    }
}
```

### Constants in Traits

```php
// ✅ Constantes en traits
trait Loggable {
    public const LOG_LEVEL_ERROR = 'error';
    public const LOG_LEVEL_INFO = 'info';
    
    public function log(string $message, string $level = self::LOG_LEVEL_INFO): void {
        error_log("[{$level}] {$message}");
    }
}

class UserService {
    use Loggable;
    
    public function process(): void {
        $this->log('Processing user', self::LOG_LEVEL_INFO);
    }
}
```

### Deprecate Dynamic Properties

```php
// ✅ Declarar todas las propiedades explícitamente
class User {
    public string $name;
    public string $email;
    
    public function __construct(string $name, string $email) {
        $this->name = $name;
        $this->email = $email;
    }
}

// ❌ Evitar propiedades dinámicas
$user = new User('John', 'john@example.com');
// $user->age = 30; // Deprecated en PHP 8.2
```

## Características PHP 8.1 (Compatibles con 8.2)

### Enums

```php
// ✅ Usar enums para conjuntos fijos de valores
enum UserRole: string {
    case Admin = 'admin';
    case Editor = 'editor';
    case Subscriber = 'subscriber';
    
    public function label(): string {
        return match($this) {
            self::Admin => 'Administrador',
            self::Editor => 'Editor',
            self::Subscriber => 'Suscriptor',
        };
    }
    
    public function canEdit(): bool {
        return match($this) {
            self::Admin, self::Editor => true,
            self::Subscriber => false,
        };
    }
}

// Uso
function assignRole(User $user, UserRole $role): void {
    $user->role = $role;
}

assignRole($user, UserRole::Admin);
```

### Readonly Properties

```php
// ✅ Propiedades readonly individuales
class User {
    public function __construct(
        public readonly string $id,
        public readonly DateTime $createdAt,
        public string $name,
        public string $email
    ) {}
}

$user = new User('123', new DateTime(), 'John', 'john@example.com');
$user->name = 'Jane'; // ✅ OK
// $user->id = '456'; // ❌ Error: readonly
```

### First-class Callable Syntax

```php
// ✅ Sintaxis moderna para callables
$fn = strlen(...);
$result = $fn('hello'); // 5

// Array functions
$lengths = array_map(strlen(...), $strings);

// Métodos de instancia
$validator = $user->validate(...);
$isValid = $validator($data);
```

## Características PHP 8.0 (Compatibles con 8.2)

### Named Arguments

```php
// ✅ Argumentos nombrados para mayor claridad
function createUser(
    string $name,
    string $email,
    string $role = 'subscriber',
    bool $active = true
): User {
    // ...
}

// Uso con argumentos nombrados
$user = createUser(
    name: 'John Doe',
    email: 'john@example.com',
    role: 'admin'
);
```

### Constructor Property Promotion

```php
// ✅ Promoción de propiedades en constructor
class User {
    public function __construct(
        private string $name,
        private string $email,
        private UserRole $role = UserRole::Subscriber
    ) {}
    
    public function getName(): string {
        return $this->name;
    }
}
```

### Union Types

```php
// ✅ Union types
function process(int|float $number): int|float {
    return $number * 2;
}

function find(int|string $id): User|null {
    // ...
}
```

### Match Expression

```php
// ✅ Match expression (mejor que switch)
$message = match($status) {
    'pending' => 'Pendiente',
    'approved' => 'Aprobado',
    'rejected' => 'Rechazado',
    default => 'Desconocido'
};

// Con condiciones
$price = match(true) {
    $age < 18 => 10,
    $age >= 18 && $age < 65 => 20,
    $age >= 65 => 15,
};
```

### Nullsafe Operator

```php
// ✅ Nullsafe operator
$country = $user?->getAddress()?->getCountry()?->getName();

// Equivalente a:
$country = null;
if ($user !== null) {
    $address = $user->getAddress();
    if ($address !== null) {
        $countryObj = $address->getCountry();
        if ($countryObj !== null) {
            $country = $countryObj->getName();
        }
    }
}
```

## Strong Typing

```php
// ✅ Usar strict types
declare(strict_types=1);

// ✅ Type declarations completos
class UserService {
    public function __construct(
        private readonly DatabaseConnection $db,
        private readonly LoggerInterface $logger,
        private readonly CacheInterface $cache
    ) {}
    
    public function getUser(int $id): ?User {
        $cacheKey = "user_{$id}";
        
        // Intentar obtener de cache
        $cached = $this->cache->get($cacheKey);
        if ($cached instanceof User) {
            return $cached;
        }
        
        try {
            $data = $this->db->query('SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ?', [$id]);
            
            if (!$data) {
                return null;
            }
            
            $user = new User(
                id: $data['id'],
                name: $data['name'],
                email: $data['email'],
                role: UserRole::from($data['role'])
            );
            
            $this->cache->set($cacheKey, $user, 3600);
            
            return $user;
        } catch (DatabaseException $e) {
            $this->logger->error('Failed to fetch user', [
                'id' => $id,
                'error' => $e->getMessage()
            ]);
            throw $e;
        }
    }
    
    public function saveUser(User $user): void {
        // ...
    }
}
```

## WordPress

### Seguridad

```php
// ✅ Siempre escapar salida
echo esc_html($user_name);
echo esc_attr($field_value);
echo esc_url($link);
echo wp_kses_post($content);

// ✅ Sanitizar entrada
$clean_email = sanitize_email($_POST['email'] ?? '');
$clean_text = sanitize_text_field($_POST['name'] ?? '');

// ✅ Verificar nonces
if (!isset($_POST['_wpnonce']) || !wp_verify_nonce($_POST['_wpnonce'], 'my_action')) {
    wp_die('Security check failed');
}

// ✅ Verificar capabilities
if (!current_user_can('manage_options')) {
    wp_die('Unauthorized');
}
```

